When, in fact, a particle with an electric charge accelerates or changes direction, this "disrupts" the electromagnetic field in this particular place, a little like a nail thrown into a pond.
From this "disruption" there is an electromagnetic wave (from light, or infrared, or ultraviolet, etc.), and this wave is nothing but a photon - and therefore one of the boons "force carriers".
Field more stable
The same goes for the Higgs boson, this difference close to it is another field, the Higgs field, which must be "disturbed" for this boson to appear.
