Šimon Ornest said: "In concert, we want to collect positive energy."
What do you think of the fact that in less than a month this should be the end of the world?
It's just one of these alarming news, the kind of traps we love to fall into.
In our group The Tap Tap, we laugh rather and say that we are the only group capable of collecting a rest of positive energy in order to repel or prevent the end of the world.
In addition, you set up a completely unique project in December: three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you present this project in more detail to our readers?
It is a charitable action that we have been preparing for two years now.
We decided to use the marketing potential of the end of the Maya calendar announced for December 21 at 11:10 a.m.
On the eve of 20 December, three concerts will be held simultaneously in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will almost end at the time of the end of the Maya calendar on the island of Kiribati in the Pacific Ocean, on a 12-hour time zone ahead of us.
Who had this idea?
At first I think it was my idea, then we designed everything with our creator, Honza Augusta.
Apart from the fact that we want to collect enough positive energy to save the world, we also want, together with the public, to reflect on the state of the world that we leave our children.
At the end of the Maya calendar, we created a collection of unique objects, including shoes, T-shirts, bags, and original keys against the end of the world, by buying them online at www.e-tap.cz people can also support us.
The Tap Tap group with other interpreters also recorded an anthem against the end of the world, entitled "End of the Canceled World " (Czech " Kontec světa zrušeno ").
She is already very popular on YouTube, will we also hear her at these charitable concerts?
Of course, all at the end, finally, if we succeed and that the end of the world does not take place ...
It will be sung simultaneously by all performers in the three concerts.
The anthems will also be joined at a given time as part of a very unique live broadcast of Czech television.
The words of this song were written by Tomáš Hanák who also played the main role of Jesus in the video, Xindl X also sings there...
How did you come to cooperate with them?
We collaborate with other personalities of the Czech show-biz, because we organize many concerts and charitable events...
We strive to have them participate intensively in these projects.
It has proved that most of them are interested in such cooperation and are amused.
What will be the benefits of these concerts against the end of the world?
To equip the Studeo training centre that is accessible to people with reduced mobility and which we have been working on within the framework of the Jedlička Institute, with the Tap association, and that for six years.
Teachers regularly visit students at Jedličkovskyv Institute and offer them activities that interest them and amuse them.
Students themselves do not have the means to go to classes, we try to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the construction of the Jedlička Institute, we will transfer this project into a new independent building.
Will several music groups and performers come up on stage at each of these concerts?
According to what criteria, have you chosen them?
We have tried to develop a program for all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague, Chinaski, Support Lesbians, Illustosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Suchý will be on stage.
