From the beginning, I felt there was a potential to change things.
The business show is full of things that copy each other.
In some ways, it makes sense: everything that is new is accepted with caution and it lasts a long time.
Rare are the original projects, and I can say that Tap Tap is one of them.
The first impression of a person who sees us for the first time is naturally pity, it's natural ...
But pity is totally useless, because people with disabilities are not suffering beings, abandoned by all, that we must take pity.
They are people who can live a whole life and thrive, provided they have the necessary means.
I often say that when people with disabilities come to realize something, it is not only an advance for them but for society as a whole.
